sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M31512
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: section of M13.1 (HpaI to BamHI section)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: We are designing a refactored M13 that we are calling M13.1, we decided to do the refactoring of the genome by sectors bordered by unique restriction sites on the M13K07 genome, this is to ensure that the M13.1 we design is modular enough that we can easily revert to the original section if the refactored section is unsucessful.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Emmanuel Lorenzo de los Santos
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Comes from a modified M13K07 genome sequence
